3. If a Pokemon faints it is considered dead and must either be placed in a box or released.

text:
Oooh a piece of advice... 
Not evolving your mons until later is actually not a horrible idea.

Piplup learns some moves much earlier as it is now than it will after it evolves...

Example: It learns Hydro Pump at LV 43
as a prinplup is learns it at LV 50
and as an Empoleon it learns it at LV 59

Plus your piplup will take less Exp to level up at weaker evolutions meaning it grows faster.
This means that you can make the game harder for yourself by waiting until later to evolve but then get stronger moves to make up for that. And then steamroll the rest of the game.




Edit: I said a wrong thing.

text:
Okay, so not really related, but I had a weird dream about Gura last night.
I was at some sort of office, near a customer help desk, when a 3-4 foot tall Gura walks in and starts to tell me something. A co-worker interrupted and said "hey, I've got a box of matches," and ⅓ of the people in the office proceeded to burn their cubicle down, while the others kept working (the fire didn't spread or have any smoke, apparently). Anyway, Gura was now very sad and told me she lost her stuffed animal, shark-a-shark (I think that was the name?) with irresistible puppy-dog eyes. I promised to get it back, and started looking all over the office. I teleported to a medium-size store, with a cinematic, third-person camera angle, and neat to the dry ice was a purple stuffed animal that wasn't a shark, though I can't remember what it was. In a thought bubble, I gave the new animal to Gura, and she was still sad, but thanked me anyway. Then I gave it to her, and she was happy as can be, thanking me profusely.
Then I went on an adventure with a strange kid near a local skate park to find something (presumably the original), then Max Payne and different videogame characters from different eras fought each other in a big building, went to the reoccurring dream-mall for a minute I think, but that stuff's unrelated. Anyway, I hope Gura finds Shark-a-shark (or was it Shark-shack?) soon and in good health!
